<recipe>
<title>
Easy Chocolate Cupcakes
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1/4 cup butter , at cool room temperature
1 cup granulated sugar
2 oz . semisweet baking chocolate
2 large eggs , at room temperature
2 large egg yolks , at room temperature
1/2 cup + 1 tablespoon vegetable oil
1 tablespoon vanilla extract
1/3 cup full-fat sour cream
1 cup all-purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 cup cocoa powder natural or Dutch processed
1/2 cup room temperature water
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease or line 16 muffin cups. Set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar until combined.
Melt the chocolate in the microwave or in a double boiler.
Once chocolate has cooled to room temperature, add it to the butter/sugar mixture. Mix until just combined.
Stir in eggs and egg yolks one at a time until just combined.
Add oil, vanilla, and sour cream. Stir until just combined.
Whisk together flour, salt, baking soda, and cocoa powder into a separate medium-sized bowl. 
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.
Stir in water until just combined.
Divide batter among prepared muffin cups, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 15-25 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Remove cupcakes, and place on wire cooling rack. 
Once cooled, frost with desired frosting. 
</instructions>
</recipe>
